From Tom Haapanen Subject RFD misc setup This is the official Request for Discussion RFD for the creation of two new newsgroups for Microsoft Windows This is a second RFD replacing the one originally posted in January ' and never taken to a vote The proposed groups are described below NAME STATUS PURPOSE Discussions about setting up and installing Windows NT and about system and peripheral compatability issues for Windows NAME STATUS PURPOSE Miscellaneous non programming discussions about using Windows NT including issues such as security networking features console mode and Windows RATIONALE Microsoft NT is the newest member of the Microsoft Windows family of operating systems or operating environments for those who wish to argue about the meaning of an OS The family ranges from Modular Windows through Windows and Windows for Workgroups to Windows NT at the high To date Microsoft has shipped over beta copies and pre release SDKs of Windows NT the actual release is slated for May June ' While Windows NT has an entirely new design internally it shares an application programming interface with the other members of the Windows family its API includes the API used in Win dows and the API subset less threads networking and security can be used to create bit applications for Windows The user interface is also practically identical to that of Windows with the addition of logins and a few other It uses Program Manager File Manager and other applets and generally pre sents an identical appearance to the Many of the announced Windows NT applications are ports of existing Windows apps and NT also runs existing Thus it appears logical that Windows NT should share the following groups with the other members of the Windows family The following groups are also clearly applicable to Windows NT as well as Windows In conclusion the only clear argument for the separation of the Windows and Windows NT hierarchies is different internal structures of Windows and Windows And yet operating systems such as OS Macintosh OS Xenix and Coherent all have undergone major rewrites without having been split into separate newsgroup Further Windows is due for a major rewrite itself in when the fully bit protected mode and with DOS built in next generation Windows Chicago debuts next year surely it should remain in the same And what then would be the jus tification for separating Windows NT from other Windows versions DISCUSSION PERIOD The discussion period will run from April to May VOTING The CFV Call for Votes will be issued around May based on the feedback received during the discussion No votes will be accepted prior to the tom haapanen software metrics inc waterloo ont stick your index fingers into both corners of your now pull that's how the corrado makes you car january '